<Paintings>
  <Text 190 -130 12 #000000 0 "Generated current pulse:\n\n1.2 μA * 10 ns = 12 fC  \n\nfor the LGAD assumed:\n- gain = 10\n- thickness fraction = 5\n--> factor 2\n">
  <Text 120 430 12 #000000 0 "Op.Amp. and Resistor with the short\nto try what happens\nif removing or not the component.\n\nThe typical conf is:\n- no op.amp\n- no resistor\n(so both with the short to "disable" them)\n\nWhat seems needed\nwhen putting something below\n(i.e. the SiMS-LGAD series) is\n- to add the resistor\n- still the Op.Amp. is just to try (keep the short on it)\n\nAlso the diode (both direction) doesn't solve\nthe problem on the neighbor strips.\nI didn't check if (in the right direction)\nif, with the SiMS-LGAD series, at least\nsolves the bias issue\n">
</Paintings>
